cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Research Swarm: A Configurable Multi-Agent Research Framework"
message: >-
  If you use this software in your research, please cite it using
  the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Damien
    family-names: Huzard
    alias: dhuzard
    affiliation: Independent Researcher
version: 0.2.0
date-released: "2026-04-09"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/dhuzard/piu-psych-swarm"
abstract: >-
  Research Swarm is a configuration-driven multi-agent research framework
  built on LangGraph. It deploys an autonomous team of AI specialists
  (orchestrator, domain experts, journalist, adversarial reviewer) that
  search databases, synthesise evidence, and produce citable research
  manuscripts — all customisable through a single YAML file without
  modifying Python code.
keywords:
  - multi-agent systems
  - large language models
  - scientific research automation
  - LangGraph
  - autonomous agents
  - systematic review
